ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Very useful as a first systematic introduction to a subject that is essential in many other fields.
TAKE IT! Covers important material and covers it well.
This is a very important course in analysis, giving the fundamentals for integration.
If you expect to advanced measure thoery, it is inappropriate.
I would not recommend because almost all of the mateiral covered in this course would be covered in a faster way in a course like Advanced Probability, for example.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: For a Statistics student, measure theory is essential to understand probability theory rigourously. This course provided an introduction to the subject.
Helps to understand measure theory, which is useful for prob. It also covers important material for functional analysis which is really useful for more applied fields like statistics and economics.
